He later stormed on to the line of fire and led the line forward before running alone to a field shooter and shutting down three members of the detachment.
Lieutenant-Colonel Vann was killed by a German sniper on October 4, 1918, just over a month before the end of the war.
Michael Vann, 72, said his grandfather’s actions were “something I know I can never touch, but also something that makes me feel humble.”
